Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add the
@Basmati Rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side
until ready to serve.

== Meat and Peppers ==

Meanwhile, halve the @Green Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin
strips, then chop into roughly 1cm pieces.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @British Beef Mince{240%g}, @Central American Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}
and sliced pepper. Fry until the mince has browned, ~{5-6%mins}. Use a #spoon{} to break
up the mince as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

== Assembly ==

While the mince cooks, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{40%g}.

Once the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the garlic to the mince and cook for ~{1%min} more.

Stir through the @Tomato Passata{1%carton}, @Chicken Stock Paste{10%g},
@sugar{1%tsp} and @water{100%ml} for the sauce (see pantry for both amounts).

Simmer until the sauce has thickened slightly, ~{3-4%mins}.

== Finishing ==

Stir the @BBQ Sauce{32%g} through the mince and cook until thickened and warmed
through, ~{1-2%mins}.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if you feel it needs it. Add a splash of
water if it's a little too thick.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}.

When everything's ready, share the rice between your #serving bowls{}.

Top with the BBQ beef stew.

Scatter over the cheese to finish. Enjoy!